args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor chapter 11 of the main campaign.
Hee hee! Success! Now to find Master\nXuan Zang somewhere in this castle...
Unknown individual detected.\nPossibility of intruder: High.
Good heavens! It moves and talks!
Are you powered by clockwork? Perhaps a\nseries of water channels and gates?\nOh, I simply MUST learn your secrets!
I am not certain what you desire,\nbut your proposal is refused.
Perhaps I'll glean this bio-form's secrets\nif I disassemble it! Ah, but I'm a genius.\nNow where did I put that screwdriver...?
Disassembling? This will likely result\nin my ultimate destruction.
Target confirmed as hostile.\nInterceptor program activated.
▷Laxi, wait! You don't have to—◁\nOverruled. Eliminating hostile.
Blargh! ...H-heavens, what a blow!\nAlmost...like a master...
Hey, boss? Don't wanna bug ya,\nbut one'a Xuan Zang's buddies was\ncollapsed over in the courtyard.

Oh! Hello, Your Highness! My, but it has
been quite a while. It was SUCH a
pleasure making your acquaintance
during the whole Mei Hou Wang incident.
Well, after that unpleasantness was over,\nI determined that Master Xuan Zang was\nstaying here and came to see her.
Okay, I get all that. The part I'm confused\nabout is where you were lying in a heap\non the ground while moaning in pain.
WAS I doing that? My word!\nI fear my memory gets a bit fuzzy just\nafter I secreted into your castle here.
Yes, well, I'm clearly standing now,\nso let us leave the past in the past.\nNow then, please take me to Xuan Zang!
Xuan Zang isn't here right now.
She found another dangerous relic\nand went out to seal it.
She DID?! When?! Where?! Why?!\nAnd what sort of relic?!
A mystery relic, eh? HmmmmMMMMM...\nWell, it will be no easy thing to track\nher down if that is her goal.
I suppose there is nothing to do but wait\nin this lovely castle for her return.
Well, we'd be happy to have you.\nTake any empty room you like.

I deeply appreciate your kindness, sir!
It may be presumptuous of me to offer
thanks, but I would be thrilled to apply
my prodigious talents to your cause!
I have much experience from my days\nin Taiwu as a tactician, public servant,\nand technician.
I can be of service not only in battle,\nbut in running the castle as well.
That's quite the offer! We'd be happy to\ntake whatever help you can provide.
It is my pleasure. My...GREAT pleasure.\nNow then, I must be off. Ta-taaaaa!
Please tell me you did not invite that\nmad weapon creator to stay here in\nthe castle.

What if he creates poison smoke that
paralyzes people or some other horrific
thing? Don't you remember how much
trouble we had last time?
Uh...yeaaaah. I probably should\nhave thought of that, huh?
When I think about all those horrid little\nweapons he keeps on his person...
Well, I just hope nothing happens—\nbut I cannot say I am confident.
Thanks for the heads-up, Cleo.\nI promise to keep a close eye on him.
How simply FASCINATING! Might the\ntwo of you mind telling me more of the\nHalidom's secrets, hmmmMMMM?
Of course! It has been speculated that\nthe Halidom is actually a structure of\nalmost impossible age.
We believe magic was used to prevent\ntime-related deterioration and keep it\nas you see it now. Additionally...
Sha Wujing seems to be getting on\nwith the other scholars well enough.
I'm glad. Maybe everything is going\nto be all right after all.
Yes, because it would be most intolerable\nif he started causing trouble immediately\nupon his arrival. *cough*

My, what a WONDERFUL miscalculation!
To think I would come across such strange
technology after following Master Xuan
Zang all this way!
Do any other secrets cling to this castle?\nI've never seen anything quite like...
Wait. ...Er, wait? Yes, wait! Hooo!\nI remember you! You were waiting\nfor me when I first entered this place!
▷Sorry for what Laxi did earlier—that\nwas way uncalled for. Are you hurt?◁
The automaton! Oh, I DO remember you!
▷Okay, Laxi. Apologize to this man.◁\nNegative. I was not at fault.
Heavens above! The mechanism\nis arguing with ITSELF!
Laxi has two hearts in one body.
I've never HEARD of such technology!\nOooo, I simply MUST disassemble it\nat once to discern its secrets!
Er, yes? Disassembly? I simply take this\nlittle doll apart and find out what makes\nit ＂tick,＂ as they say in the business.
Come here, you! Let me start by removing\nyour chest cavity so I may see the inner\nworkings of your dual hearts!
Or perhaps I will do the same with you.
S-such strength! Such movements!\nI knew the machine could fight,\nbut I had no idea it could do THIS!
Gahhh! Wait, what did WE do?!
I hate to be one of those I-told-you-so\npeople, but I clearly told him so.

Perhaps the problem lies not with
Sha Wujing's weapons, but with the
man himself. Trouble just seems to
follow him like a raincloud...
